00:13:03,149 --> 00:13:05,385
(growling)

278
00:13:07,787 --> 00:13:10,023
Look, over there!

279
00:13:10,023 --> 00:13:12,325
Incoming!

280
00:13:12,325 --> 00:13:14,360
♪

281
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:16,029
Oh, well, so much for Plan A,

282
00:13:16,029 --> 00:13:19,465
but, like I always say,
there's always tomorrow, right?

283
00:13:19,465 --> 00:13:21,367
♪

284
00:13:21,367 --> 00:13:23,403
They've got us surrounded!

285
00:13:23,403 --> 00:13:26,773
♪

286
00:13:26,773 --> 00:13:28,941
(yelling gibberish)

287
00:13:28,941 --> 00:13:35,782
♪

288
00:13:39,285 --> 00:13:40,920
Mocchi!

289
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:42,955
♪

290
00:13:42,955 --> 00:13:45,458
‐'chi!
‐Pixie!

291
00:13:45,458 --> 00:13:48,428
Can't complain about
that kind of timing, huh?

292
00:13:48,428 --> 00:13:51,664
♪

293
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:53,232
Let's go!

294
00:13:53,232 --> 00:13:59,005
♪

295
00:13:59,005 --> 00:14:00,540
Genki.

296
00:14:00,540 --> 00:14:02,542
♪

297
00:14:02,542 --> 00:14:05,311
Come and get me!

298
00:14:05,311 --> 00:14:07,313
(grunting)

299
00:14:07,313 --> 00:14:36,109
♪

300
00:14:36,109 --> 00:14:39,078
(creaking)

301
00:14:39,078 --> 00:15:02,702
♪

302
00:15:02,702 --> 00:15:05,004
(screaming)

303
00:15:05,004 --> 00:15:06,939
(grumbling)

304
00:15:06,939 --> 00:15:08,975
(panting)

305
00:15:08,975 --> 00:15:19,185
♪

306
00:15:19,185 --> 00:15:21,120
(laughing)

307
00:15:21,120 --> 00:15:33,266
♪

308
00:15:33,266 --> 00:15:34,901
Alley‐oop!

309
00:15:34,901 --> 00:15:38,204
♪

310
00:15:38,204 --> 00:15:40,673
Ahh!

311
00:15:40,673 --> 00:15:42,675
(grunting)

312
00:15:42,675 --> 00:15:44,076
Not bad, huh?

313
00:15:44,076 --> 00:15:46,779
Now let's go back
and find the others.

314
00:15:46,779 --> 00:15:49,482
♪

315
00:15:49,482 --> 00:15:50,683
What was that?

316
00:15:50,683 --> 00:15:53,453
♪

317
00:15:53,453 --> 00:15:55,655
(screaming)

318
00:15:55,655 --> 00:16:01,060
♪

319
00:16:01,060 --> 00:16:03,796
Look, there's the exit!

320
00:16:03,796 --> 00:16:26,052
♪

321
00:16:26,052 --> 00:16:27,420
Surrender!

322
00:16:27,420 --> 00:16:30,356
♪

323
00:16:30,356 --> 00:16:32,091
Lightning!

324
00:16:32,091 --> 00:16:34,160
(explosions)

325
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:41,400
♪

326
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:42,435
(together)
Chicken!

327
00:16:42,435 --> 00:16:45,438
♪

328
00:16:45,438 --> 00:16:47,640
Mocchi, you're safe now!

329
00:16:47,640 --> 00:16:49,408
Pixie good, 'chi!

330
00:16:49,408 --> 00:16:51,511
♪

331
00:16:51,511 --> 00:16:52,879
Thanks.

332
00:16:52,879 --> 00:17:05,091
♪

333
00:17:05,091 --> 00:17:06,759
Whoa.

334
00:17:06,759 --> 00:17:14,166
♪

335
00:17:14,166 --> 00:17:16,602
Yo gang, all the
rides are working,

336
00:17:16,602 --> 00:17:18,971
and we've got the whole
place to ourselves!

337
00:17:18,971 --> 00:17:20,907
Think of the fun we can have!

338
00:17:20,907 --> 00:17:24,043
Yeah, and think of all
the money we're gonna save!

339
00:17:24,043 --> 00:17:26,145
(gasping)

340
00:17:26,145 --> 00:17:28,314
♪

341
00:17:28,314 --> 00:17:30,182
Wow!

342
00:17:30,182 --> 00:17:33,452
♪

343
00:17:33,452 --> 00:17:36,022
Wow.

344
00:17:36,022 --> 00:17:38,791
‐Ahh.
‐Ahhh.

345
00:17:38,791 --> 00:17:41,394
♪

346
00:17:41,394 --> 00:17:44,263
There's so much to do,
I don't know where to start!

347
00:17:44,263 --> 00:17:46,299
No kidding!

348
00:17:46,299 --> 00:17:55,207
♪

349
00:17:55,207 --> 00:17:57,343
Huh‐‐what happened?

350
00:17:57,343 --> 00:18:01,447
♪

351
00:18:01,447 --> 00:18:03,549
Hey, who turned out the lights?

352
00:18:03,549 --> 00:18:06,252
Aww.

353
00:18:06,252 --> 00:18:07,720
Huh?

354
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:09,388
♪

355
00:18:09,388 --> 00:18:11,857
'chi.

356
00:18:11,857 --> 00:18:19,765
♪

357
00:18:19,765 --> 00:18:23,102
I knew it was too
good to be true.

358
00:18:23,102 --> 00:18:25,171
Golem sad.

359
00:18:25,171 --> 00:18:28,007
This must've been such a blast,

360
00:18:28,007 --> 00:18:30,576
but now it's just
a bunch of ruins.

361
00:18:30,576 --> 00:18:34,714
Maybe one day it'll be restored
and the people will return.

362
00:18:34,714 --> 00:18:38,084
It'll happen, as soon
as we find the Phoenix.

363
00:18:38,084 --> 00:18:40,987
Except that we're
running out of time.

364
00:18:40,987 --> 00:18:42,321
Huh?

365
00:18:42,321 --> 00:18:44,824
Moo has excavated his body.

366
00:18:44,824 --> 00:18:48,327
‐Are you serious?
‐I am.

367
00:18:48,327 --> 00:18:52,064
That's what I came
here to tell you guys.

368
00:18:52,064 --> 00:18:53,899
You're leaving?

369
00:18:53,899 --> 00:18:55,701
Big Blue is
researching the Phoenix,

370
00:18:55,701 --> 00:18:58,304
so I'm going right
now to meet him.

371
00:18:58,304 --> 00:19:00,339
We share the same
feelings as you.

372
00:19:00,339 --> 00:19:02,708
Let's crush Moo's evil plans,

373
00:19:02,708 --> 00:19:06,078
and one day the world
will be peaceful once again.

374
00:19:06,078 --> 00:19:18,824
♪

375
00:19:18,824 --> 00:19:19,925
Yeah!

376
00:19:19,925 --> 00:19:22,461
Okay, let's move out, gang!

377
00:19:22,461 --> 00:19:26,265
♪

378
00:19:26,265 --> 00:19:29,735
(wind howling)

379
00:19:29,735 --> 00:19:34,173
In other words, the ancient
wars wiped out everything,

380
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:37,810
and they were
completely meaningless.

381
00:19:37,810 --> 00:19:41,180
They were extremely foolish.

382
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:44,917
(evil laughter)

383
00:19:44,917 --> 00:19:45,951
Take him away!

384
00:19:45,951 --> 00:19:48,387
No, please wait!

385
00:19:48,387 --> 00:19:51,557
Please, listen to
what I have to say!

386
00:19:51,557 --> 00:19:52,892
Stop!

387
00:19:52,892 --> 00:19:55,828
So that light was
the final gate.

388
00:19:55,828 --> 00:19:57,897
If the light
caused a separation,

389
00:19:57,897 --> 00:20:01,300
then surely it can
cause things to merge.

390
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:04,670
Come to think of it, I remember
hearing something about some

391
00:20:04,670 --> 00:20:06,806
ancient ruins in
the Torles Mountains

392
00:20:06,806 --> 00:20:09,208
just like the ones in the story!

393
00:20:09,208 --> 00:20:11,577
I suppose it could be true.

394
00:20:11,577 --> 00:20:15,047
Take the floating castle
and bring the ruins to me.

395
00:20:15,047 --> 00:20:17,016
Right away, Master!

396
00:20:17,016 --> 00:20:19,885
(wind howling)

397
00:20:19,885 --> 00:20:26,759
♪

398
00:20:26,759 --> 00:20:29,228
(laughing)

399
00:20:31,130 --> 00:20:34,967
The day I look forward to will
have to wait a little longer

400
00:20:34,967 --> 00:20:39,238
for the return of
the floating castle.

401
00:20:39,238 --> 00:20:47,046
♪

402
00:20:47,046 --> 00:20:48,280
♪ Monsters ♪

403
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:49,849
♪ Monsters rule ♪

404
00:20:49,849 --> 00:21:14,440
♪

